name: Family Portrait

description:
Henry Franklin, a Black Hills tourist photographer, has suffered a mysterious death, and his corpse was found in an advanced state of mummification. When FBI Special Agents Fox Mulder and Dana Scully begin their investigation, they discover the possibility that Franklin is somehow linked to a series of mysterious maladies that struck people who had their photographs taken by him. And that some people who had him take their pictures had disappeared!

As the investigation continues, Fox Mulder finds himself becoming inexplicably fascinated with Franklin's old portrait camera. Somehow, the facts they need to solve the mystery involve that camera. The question is, will the camera help the agents solve the mystery, or make them victims?
name: Family Portrait - Part Two: The Camera Eye
The Kanashibari
Donor

description: Scully and Mulder encounter fashion victims of the fatal kind.
name: Silver Lining
Be Prepared, Part Two
Remote Control, Part One

description: Scully and Mulder must find a killer who strips the flesh of his victims.
name: Surrounded, Part 1

description: Variant photo cover - see pic below.
name: Soma
Skybuster

description: This issue has no title in the comic, but was supposed to be called: The Face of Extinction.

name: Devil's Advocate

description:
Last issue.

Art cover artist: Miran Kim
Variant:  Photo Cover  -  see pic below. (John Cruz)
name: Severed

description:
The third Crypt of Dawn anthology includes the following stories:

  • Death
  • Infinite Variety
  • Awakenings
  • Collision.

The most eagerly-awaited storyline begins in this month's issue of Dark Horse Presents! They are the galaxy's most deadly alien races; now, the time has come for them to meet at last! It's the Aliens and Predator together in one story! The confrontation of the century brought to you by Randy Stradley and film designer (The Abyss and Robocop II) Phillip Norwood! The story will then continue in a full-color miniseries coming out next month! Also, Paul Guinan and Anina Bennet continue the story of The Heartbreakers--beautiful and deadly clones! Plus, the further "sword and sorcery" adventures of Delia and Celia by Gary Davis!

Chapters

Aliens vs. Predator

Delia & Celia - The Great Marsh

Heartbreakers - Ceiling Zero
name: Aliens vs. Predator; Heartbreakers; Delia & Celia

description: Dinah (Black Canary) showed up at Barbara's, which made for an embarrassing moment for the showering Mr. Grayson. Soames planned on using one of the prison guards, Helzinger (aka Amygdala), to escape (he knew his past). Shrike captured Nightwing.
name: Stalked

description:
Overview

Captured by the minions of Shrike, Nightwing comes face-to-face with the one man who has dedicated his life to exterminating the former Robin. Chained in a warehouse, surrounded by deadly ninjas and staring into the face of his archenemy -- how in the world is Nightwing going to get out of this one?
 
 Shrike holds Nightwing captive, reveals who he is, and tries to run NW's fingerprints. Fortunately, Babs has a system set up for fake names and such to appear when Bat people's fingerprints are run. And she is alerted. Babs and Black Canary set out to find and rescue Nightwing. Nightwing manages to get himself loose but now faces Shrike and many ninjas...
name: Yesterday Never Dies

description: Nightwing's history comes back to haunt him, as Shrike (from ROBIN: YEAR ONE) and Shrike's gaggle of deadly ninjas have Dick completely outmatched.  Meanwhile, Oracle dispatches Black Canary to rescue Nightwing from capture.  But when Canary makes it to the scene, will it already be too late?
name: A World of Hate

description: Nightwing began searching for Freddy Minh. He snuck into Minh's home and found babies in incubators. Mrs. Minh revealed to him that they were the embryos that he'd saved from Black Mask's gang during his first days in Bludhaven. She also revealed to him that she'd killed Freddy years ago. She asked Nightwing to leave her home and not return.
name: Where's Freddy Minh?

description: As the Transbelvan Mafia moved into town, Dick got his badge and became a full-fledged cop. He remained partnered with Amy and she invited him into a circle of honest cops trying to take down the crooked ones.
name: The Threshold

description: Dick and Amy went in after a man who could squeal on a bad cop, but the bad cop shot him before they could do anything with it.
name: Lethal Force

description: Nightwing's whirly-bat was shot down as he entered the Slab. He thought back on previous encounters with the Joker as he crashed and began his search. On the way in, he was attacked by Jokerized inmates, but easily took care of them.
name: Midnight Madness: A Last Laugh Jaunt

description: Blue Beetle and Robin cleaned up a few more Jokerized goons, including Fleeter. Dick continued to blame himself for going too far against Joker. Flash visited him and reminded him who he was.
name: Red, Fright, and Blue

description:
Overview

When ancient death cults and mushroom gods vie with fast food restaurants and infomercials for dominance of mankind, a 1500-year-old warrior must return to life to preserve the natural order. Owing equally to 1930s pulp fiction and 1970s horror comics, fan-favorite Batman artist Kelley Jones introduces an outlandish hero in an eerie, action-packed tale on the cutting edge of adventure comics.
name: Red Dreams

description:
Overview

A cosmic evil has risen up out of the earth, and the Hammer must put it back down. Kelley Jones combines classical horror sensibilities with exciting new ideas to push the envelope on occult adventure.
name: A Field of Blackbirds

description:
Ragged Robin has departed in a time machine on a mission to the future with the distraught, lovelorn King Mob relinquishing his weapons on a Himalayan retreat. Meanwhile, Boy leaves the team in an effort to reclaim a normal life for herself, Jack Frost prepares for more training with Jolly Roger at the Invisibles training center in North Africa, and Lord Fanny embarks on a quest for revenge.

Come, Armageddon. Come.
name: Satanstorm One: common people

description: Learn the secret history of Division X, as the conspiracy cops search for the Royal Monster, not to mention their main man, Detective Flint, who was abducted and tortured last issue. Meanwhile, King Mob travels from India to Delhi to swap stories with Mister Six and swap spit with a pretty new Invisible.
name: Satanstorm Two: cold britannia

description: The Invisibles regroup to help Division X locate Flint, the abducted conspiracy cop, while the Royal Monster gets closer to claiming his throne. Meanwhile, as Ragged Robin continues her voyage home to the future, a beautiful and mysterious rocket scientist sets her sights on King Mob.
name: Satanstorm Three: the "it" girls

description: King Mob and the newest Invisible team up to save Inspector Flint from a harrowing death. Meanwhile, Lord Fanny finds a new friend and Jack Frost uncovers a connection between Barbelith and the C.I.A.
name: Satanstorm Four: digging up Beryl

description: As the Marquis de Sade's vision of the future is exposed, King Mob travels to India where he visits Lady Edith for the last time. Plus, the shocking truth is revealed about the owner of the Hand of Glory, the identity of the Harliquinade, and which Invisibles team member attempted suicide!
name: Karmageddon Part One: Tantrika

description: In India, King Mob and Lady Edith discover the missing Hand of Glory--the powerful severed extremity that has the power to hasten the apocalypse. This would normally be a good thing--except they've found it reattached to its unlikely owner.
name: Karmageddon Part Two: type Ω

description: India's in flames as Jack Frost and Lord Fanny welcome a former Invisible back on the scene--but will Ragged Robin cause friction between King Mob and his new partner in crime?
name: Karmageddon Part Three: six minus six

description: There's a traitor in the Invisibles, one who joins Forces with the Cyphermen. Plus, King Mob has his final confrontation with his inner psyche as Edith takes her last breath in India.
name: Karmageddon Part Four: smile

description: Ragged Robin, former group leader and telepathic witch, returns from the future coveting secret information that could change the 21st century--not to mention King Mob's psychedelic-Romeo lifestyle.
name: The Invisible Kingdom Part One: Planet Stepford

description: Fashion and politics collide as the Royal Monster gets prepped, Helga gets preened, and King Mob and the Invisibles get to be the ultimate royal party crashers.
name: The Invisible Kingdom Part 2: Goodbye Rag

description:
The aftermath of the bloody coronation leaves King Mob, Jack and Lord Fanny shattered in the UK, which can only mean one thing: Ragged Robin to the rescue.

The second last issue in the run when the series acutally counts down for 12 to 1. This issue is also one of the few times where when being collected in Trade Paperback a few pages are redrawn and altered. In this case the three Ashley Wood pages that were later redrawn by Cameron Stewart for the collected Trade Paperback: The Invisibles, Volume 3, The Invisible Kingdom.

Below are the side by side comparison of Ashley Wood's pages verses Cameron Stewart's.

All the words bubbles and the number of panels are the same in both versions in the above comparison. No words are changed in both the above and below versions. The only real difference is an additional panel is present in Ashley Wood's version. This could be a minor thing and something that was not in the script anyway. The main symbols and key visuals are present in both versions. All Cameron Stewart really did was exaggerate certain things, like the mother and her baby. Ashley Wood's pages stuck to a presentation with more shadows.

Only really in the third and final page of Ashley Wood's contributes are completely changed. The number of panels extend from Five to Six and the visual presentation and ideas are very different. Only in the third page it is clear Grant Morrison was not happy with Ashley Wood's original pages.

The Cameron Stewart pages are considered the true version since they were redone for the Trade. Ashley Wood's pages are interesting because they were a different interpretation of the same script.
name: The Invisible Kingdom Part 3: The Moment of the Blitz

description: The ultimate conspiracy series comes to a grand finish as the team reunites in a future that is above and beyond any great expectations.
name: Glitterdämmerung

description: A provacative new series in the tradition of PREACHER and TRANSMETROPOLITAN begins. A century-old pulp-fiction writer returns to America after a 25-year absence, only to find himself hunted by other members of his long-lived clan, in a new ongoing series from VERTIGO.
name: The End

description: VERTIGO's newest series continues as Story Johnson finds his way out of the Cambodian jungle and deep into the heart of a Southern bayou. Forced to rely on the kindness of a stranger, Story's got a head full of jumbled memories, a hat full of something worse and his murderous brother "Kid Gloves" stalking his every move. Meanwhile, across the country, Story's ex-lover, Ruth, a.k.a. "Sweetcakes", finds her life in imminent danger as she pursues her wayward son in his search for the fabled Johnson "place."
name: Does God Look Down?

description: Billy hooks up with a love-starved widow and her cynical son; all three are being tracked by murderous agents for various reasons. The albino antagonist of the series rambles on about his plans to his drug-dealing nurse who overhears a little too much and is killed.
name: Careless Love

description: With the road flying by, Story's memory begins to return, giving a glimpse at both the sordid and festive early times of "The Place." Ruth, on her search for Sonny, learns a little more than she bargained for about Johnson history from John Law while, unbeknownst to all, the nefarious Kid Gloves has ordered the Regulators to start closing in on everyone.
name: Need to Be Nervous

description: A little sibling rivalry, a lot of narcotics, a fast car on wet blacktop...and Story is spinning out of control and into a Texas jail, leaving Jenny and Martin MIA. In New Mexico, Ruth has her own trouble staying on the road and calls on old flame Carlos for help. While deep in the Colorado mountains, Sonny is missing Rosa and discovering that, when you are a Johnson, danger and weirdness come with the territory.
name: Two More Dead in Texas

description:
Ruth, recovering from the surprise of finding Story Johnson resurrected and back in her life, delivers him a few shocks of her own. A little family feuding forces Asa to teach Kid Gloves a lesson about respect with a punishment that will put Story and Gloves face to face.

Note: Hog Johnson's appearance is in flashback only.
name: Distant Cousins

description: Women, tequila and guns spell trouble for Story as he tries to find his son, stay out of Gloves' radar and keep it all together. When U.S. Marshals come knocking on Jenny's door for answers to the missing sheriff, Martin plays hero, "Johnson" style, and suddenly it's all about to blow up in their faces.
name: Crossfire

description: Story and his growing band, fugitives from federal justice, hide out in "Hell Holes." But once Sheriff John Law learns that Kid Gloves is family and Big Buck is still alive, it's Johnson-justice that Story needs sanctuary from. Meanwhile, trying to do right by his militant cousins and rescue his Mom and Rosa, Sonny walks straight into Kid Gloves' trap.
name: Cold, Cold, Cold

description: Story and gang get a plan of action together to take down Gloves. What better way to lure a psychopath than with a "dead" body? Problem is, Daddy has cut Gloves loose, and, if Story isn't careful, he'll be swingin' in the breeze before sunrise.
name: Strange Fruit

description: "Hate, Murder and Revenge." With Story hung up in the plot and Gloves gloating, it's up to Ruth to put a twist in the bad guy's tale. Things turn around quickly, and now it's Gloves who's facing a cruel and unusual taste of Johnson justice. The swamp of ugly violence threatens to suck everyone down. But, with Sonny still in jail, Story isn't ready to abandon his claim on the moral highground. Lucky for Kid Gloves...or maybe not.
name: Hate, Murder and Revenge

description: "Temptation." At a whistle-stop called Temptation, Story Johnson waits for a train. Still a little high from his victory over Kid Gloves, he thinks he's ready for a final high-stakes poker-game with Asa Arizona. But a nurse called Dolores knocks him a little off track and Story finds the deck stacked against him. But a quitter never wins and Story is playing for the freedom of his son; he's not going to fold now, even if he has to bet the farm.
name: Temptation

description: "Desperado." While Story's in Hell Holes trying to put a beneficial spin on his dubious deal with Old Asa, Reverend Hell is working on persuading Sonny he has a vocation in the Church of Johnson. With every one so preoccupied, no one notices that Martin's disappeared with a bad disposition and a bottle of whiskey.
name: Desperado

description: "The Devil Kid" has barely gotten clear of Hell Holes, toting John Law's pistol and a head full of dark confusion, when he comes across sexy young Phoenix artist Lola Todd, with one of her roadkill art installations. Martin is in for a shock: There are worse things to scrape up and bag than gum and fast- food wrappers.
name: 100 Dead Miles #23

description: Martin "The Devil Kid" is sliding down the slippery slope to Hell in a welter of blood and gore, and it looks as if Lola is along for the ride. With the Feds closing in with lethal force, Jenny is terrified for her son. She knows time is running out, but the situation is beyond her influence, and she is losing faith in Story. Story knows his own deadline is looming and he should be writing a way out of this mess...but does he have the words to do it?
name: Every Picture...

description: Under siege by armed federal agents in a fortified Phoenix house, "Devil Kid," "Bad Momma," "Sick Twist," and Lola wait out a dark night of the soul with Story. Story knows he has only six hours to make good on his deal with Old Asa and deliver a new Billy Bad News tale, or Martin is dead at dawn. But with Jenny cool on him, Ruth in Taos, and the outrageous Nurse Dolores unattainable on his father's team, it looks like it's down to Lola put some lead in his pencil and inspire his reluctant creativity.
name: Deadline

description: "Quicksand." With Old Asa's six-gun to her head, Nurse Dolores wishes she'd stayed out of Story Johnson's story. But when the hammer falls on an empty chamber, and the Devil Kid and Lola survive their "blaze of glory" exit and are forced to face their future, Dolores knows that she's too deep into the quicksand now to quit.
name: Weird Sky

description: All bets are off as events overtake Story Johnson and he has to confront the vicious truth of Old Asa's spiteful genocide. There's no more time for hiding in a fog of fine words: It's going to take hard thinking, fast footwork and considerable luck to save the Johnson spirit from extinction now. Just as well Story has Nurse Dolores along to stiffen his resolve.
name: A Time to Be Born

description: Final issue. In "The Impossible Dream," the whirlwind has been reaped, the icons smashed, and the chickens have all found their roosts. The slate has been cleaned, and the future is ripe to be written by anyone with the vision for the job. Story Johnson has the vision; but does he have the guts to seize the time and lead the Outlaw Nation back from the brink of extinction?
name: Straight to Hell

description: THIS IS THE BOOK THE FANS DEMANDED! Before its publication date, GoGirl! generated enormous buzz on the internet in the form of interviews and rave advance reviews. Excited fans couldn't wait to buy it and read it. But evidently direct-sales retailers don't surf the net. Low advance orders made our original plans for a full-color book an impossibility. What happened next surprised and encouraged us. Fans sent us e-mails, wrote articles on the net, expressing their disapointment, offering help, even pledging a word-of-mouth and internet campaign to help GoGirl! See print. And we've taken them up on it! Starting in August, and every four months after that, you can now follow the adventures of teen superheroine GoGirl! in crisp black and white with full-color covers. Here's what Maggie Thompson had to say about GoGirl! in the Comics Buyer's Guide: " It's clearly aimed at an audience for which not much has been available...: pre-teen girls. And it should entertain that audience well....ALL the female characters (including the villain) are strong and resourceful; ...it's a comic book that could attract readers that comics have largely lost. Try it on them." GOGIRL! YOU'LL BELIEVE A GIRL CAN FLY!
name: Go Girl!

description: LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES ARCHIVES VOL. 11 continues the exciting evolution of the young galactic guardians from the 30 century. Utilizing powerfully graphic storytelling, these tales from the early 1970s combine gripping adventures with enticing interpersonal relationships. This intense hardcover includes the heroic death of a Legionnaire, the romantic development of Brainiac 5 and Supergirl's relationship, the ominous return of the Legion of Super-Villains, the retirement of a legendary Legionnaire, and an engaging adventure of the Legion of Substitute Heroes.
name: Volume 11

description: Inspired by an all new Frank Frazetta painting (which graces the cover) comes the Jaguar God. Created and written by Glenn Danzig, Jaguar God features art by popular Punisher artist Frank Teran and is the story of a primal warrior of the Amazon Jungles. A blend of South American folklore and the supernatural makes this an exciting and unique character book.
The Jaguar God is taken captive by cultists and used in their tribal sex rituals to manifest the feared empress, X'alpen, from another, darker, dimension!
The land of the Jaguar comes under attack by venturing white men. Can Jaguar God stop their destruction? Don't be caught without this exciting issue! Cover by Martin Emond.
The return of the deadly empress X'alpen. She has a surprise up her bosom for the Jaguar God. The art of Liam Sharp will simply blow you away. Cover by Martin Emond.
Jaguar God must now face X'alpen and Ba-al who the dreaded empress has brought back to life with sorcery. Can even Jaguar God defeat both these giants?

Jaguar God faces off with the Green Jaguar. Will Jaguar God be defeated? Can anything stop the Green Jaguar from devouring the villagers? Jaguar God #7 features an all new cover by Frank Frazetta.

Villagers are being mauled to death by a mysterious predator. Jaguar God takes up arms to stop the beast from killing again, but the creature may be more powerful than even the Jaguar God has bargained for.

Virtual pets. Sure they're annoying, but life-threatening? Fused with the hopes and futuristic dreams of their creator, the tiny little critters come to life as gigantic monsters, stomping the heck out of everything in their paths, leaving it up to Impulse to figure out how to save the day.
name: Virtual Pets, Virtual Heck

description: It's Halloween in Manchester, and Evil Eye gets his hands on his dad's super villain costume and equipment in order to impress the guys in a gang...which means Impulse won't be far from things, and that Halloween tricks are going to get real nasty real fast!
name: All Hallows Gettin' Even

description: Bart's mom comes back from the future to see her time-lost son, but not everybody is imbued with the spirit of the Christmas season. The odds of there being peace in Manchester are slim!
name: The Christmas Impulse

description: A Chain Lightning crossover issue. While Max Mercury wraps up some errands before he and Bart Allen join the other speedsters on their mission through time, Bart is intent on reading the book on his grandfather: The Life Story of the Flash. However, Bart’s mind quickly wanders, and he creates a world for himself where he is Barry Allen’s sidekick. In this imaginative world, Bart and Barry live together, playing video games and having fun waiting for the Flash Signal to tell them when they’re needed. Together, Bart and Barry fight not only the Rogues Gallery, but some of DC’s greatest villains. Not only is Bart the faster of the two, he is also the better strategist, and his plans allow the two of them to defeat their enemies. Helen interrupts Bart’s daydream, and Bart pleasantly confides that the book did make him feel closer to his grandfather.
name: When Barry Met Bart

description: Impulse has gotten used to being the only super hero faster than a speeding bullet in Manchester, so what's he to do when Superman's full-time life-saving brings the Man of Steel to his town? And how does Superboy fit in here?
name: Lessons in Fear

description: Riddle us this: which famous Batman foe will be leaving No Man's Land to tangle with the world's fastest kid? By the time he's done in Manchester, will the Riddler be eager to head back to Gotham City?
name: When is a Riddle not a Riddle?

description: After discovering the beauty that is April Fool's Day and the ability to get away with anything on that fine day Bart Speeds over to Gotham to test out this day for himself on Robin. But as it so happens he's not the only one in Gotham who's happy that it's April First as the Clown Prince of Crime himself sets up his own April Fools prank for Batman. So prepare yourselves for the least likely dynamic duo of Batman & Impulse.
name: First Fool's

description: The new creative team of writer Todd Dezago and artists Ethan Van Sciver and Prentis Rollins puts Bart through his paces! Forgetting a friend's birthday shouldn't be a problem for the fastest kid alive, right? The second he remembers, he can just run off and pick up the ideal gift. But when Bart forgets his buddy Preston's b-day, things don't work out quite like he hopes, since the villain known as the Fog Prince stands between Impulse and the perfect present...and the clock is ticking.
name: It's all Relative

description: Part 1 of a 2-part story featuring the son of Darkseid, Kalibak, with an art assist by the team of Walter Simonson (MANHUNTER, the upcoming ORION OF THE NEW GODS) and Scott Williams (DIVINE RIGHT: THE ADVENTURES OF MAX FARADAY)! Simonson and Williams illustrate the sequences pitting Kalibak against Max Mercury, while the series' regular art team of Ethan Van Sciver and Prentis Rollins illustrate Bart's battle with a technoplasmic creature...a fight that guarantees that Impulse's Independence Day is going to end with a bang!
name: Tumbling Down

description: Concluding a 2-part story featuring the son of Darkseid, Kalibak, with an art assist by the team of Walter Simonson (MANHUNTER, the upcoming ORION) and Scott Williams (DIVINE RIGHT: THE ADVENTURES OF MAX FARADAY)! It's Impulse versus the villain prophesied in THE LIFE STORY OF THE FLASH, Inertia, the Reverse-Impulse. Will Max Mercury make the difference? Probably not, since he's battling one of the strongest beings in the universe: Kalibak of the New Gods!
name: Threats

description: Is DAY OF JUDGMENT going to interrupt Bart's time off? Only if Hell freezes ov...uh-oh. Cameos by JSA's Golden Age Flash, Zatanna, and some demonic blasts from DC's past highlight a change-of-pace issue.
name: Night of Camping

description: Sir Real traps Impulse in a world that completely makes no sense!
name: It ain't easy being greenery

description: YOUNG JUSTICE guest-stars as Impulse... cleans up his room! How does Impulse's household chore endanger his YJ cohorts? The answers are only found here!
name: The Best of Both

description: Spend your holidays relaxing with Impulse, the JLA's Plastic Man, and Mr. Mxyzptlk, a three-man recipe for a not-so-silent night.
name: A Plastic Christmas

description: Impulse...has a cold! But fret not, world! Max Mercury's on the case. Learn more about the enigmatic speedster's past (and present) in a dizzying issue. Plus, a whimsical look at how Impulse deals with being sick in bed from writer Todd DeZago and artist Ethan van Sciver.
name: Flashing Before My Eyes

description: It's the Valentine's dance and Bart almost lost his Flash ring(that ring that contains his costume) with one of the dance rings and Arrowette makes a guest-appearance!
name: Running Rings...

description: Bart's trying to be extra good, but did he pick an extra bad time for it since there's a new super-villain in Alabama?
name: What Would The Flash Do?

description: The stars of STARS AND S.T.R.I.P.E. guest in an exciting issue of IMPULSE! Max Mercury and S.T.R.I.P.E. are trying as hard as they can to teach Impulse and the Star-Spangled Kid some valuable lessons, but some returning super-villains (including one last seen in DAY OF JUDGEMENT) may disrupt their lesson plan...forever!
name: The Sidekick Swap

description: Impulse's mentor must rely on young Bart Allen to survive in Part 1 of "Mercury Falling!" Max Mercury, so-called "Zen Master of Speed," is dying. And his only hope for salvation is the impulsive and impetuous Impulse! How will Bart's carefree life, and this series, be changed if he loses the only father he's ever known?
name: Mercury Falling, Part 1: A Question of Faith

description: Max Mercury gets medical help from Dr. Morlo and Bart works harder in school and in his missions thinking it could help Max in his recovery. Impulse goes against the Fog Prince in a short battle.
name: Mercury Falling, Part 2: Training!

description: Despite an astonishing last-ditch rescue effort, Bart must say goodbye to his oldest friend in an emotional, landmark issue.
name: Mercury Falling, Part 3: Virtual Heroes

description: Together, Impulse and Max never managed to defeat either Glory Shredder or White Lightning. With Max Mercury no longer beside him, the teen-speedster tackles them both. What's he got to prove to the world...and to himself?
name: Mercury Falling, Part 4: Bart Allen's Evil Twin

description: "Mercury Falling" reaches its shattering conclusion! How will Bart react to the traumatic events of the past few issues? The answers unfold here, in the most emotional, shocking and daring Impulse story to date!
name: Mercury Falling, Conclusion: Deathrace

description: The tear-filled epilogue to the "Mercury Falling" storyline. The JLA, JSA, Stars and S.T.R.I.P.E., and others visit Impulse in an effort to comfort him in his time of loss, and to pay their respects to a legendary hero who has fallen. How will Bart cope without his beloved mentor?
name: Friends Like These...
